<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
The present species has a separate position because the coxisternal region is completely scleritized. Sellnick &amp; Forsslund (1955) classified 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Platynothrus" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thori" subGenus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" subGenus.innerRound="1" subGenus.outerRound="1">thori</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Platynothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platynothrus</taxonomicName>
; for the moment I prefer to list the species as a 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heminothrus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
